1
00:00:19,933 --> 00:00:23,400
Tonight, a woman will re-emerge
from the shadows

2
00:00:23,467 --> 00:00:24,433
to reclaim her seat

3
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:27,100
as one of the best
in Philippine fashion,

4
00:00:27,167 --> 00:00:28,800
Celeste Diesta.

5
00:00:28,867 --> 00:00:31,600
The owner and sole creator
of Celestial.

6
00:00:31,667 --> 00:00:34,400
You know, I'm so happy
and excited about your success.

7
00:00:34,500 --> 00:00:35,933
You have come a long way.

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,367
Thank you so much for always
seeing the best in me.

9
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:42,100
He should've invested
in House of Aurelia instead.

10
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:45,700
I mean, Tonito is just throwing
away his money on Celeste.

11
00:00:45,767 --> 00:00:46,900
I don't understand

12
00:00:46,967 --> 00:00:49,500
why our clients are moving
to Aurelia.

13
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:51,367
These clients are traitors.

14
00:00:51,433 --> 00:00:52,733
They have no loyalty.

15
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:54,467
Don't let those critics
get to you.

16
00:00:54,533 --> 00:00:56,500
Remember that doing your best
is more important

17
00:00:56,567 --> 00:00:57,500
than being the best.

18
00:00:57,567 --> 00:00:59,800
Well, hello there.

19
00:00:59,867 --> 00:01:02,600
I've heard
that you are also invited

20
00:01:02,667 --> 00:01:06,633
to my former sister-in-law's
grand birthday celebration.

21
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:09,433
You should've watched your
Auntie Celeste's fashion show.

22
00:01:09,533 --> 00:01:11,033
I don't need to pretend, Dad.

23
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:11,867
I don't like her.

24
00:01:13,767 --> 00:01:14,400
Enjoy your date.

25
00:01:16,867 --> 00:01:17,500
So sorry about that.

26
00:01:19,267 --> 00:01:19,667
It's fine.

27
00:01:54,133 --> 00:01:54,433
Love,

28
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:59,033
I already called Tiffany
and I reprimanded her.

29
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:01,833
But she still owes you
an apology.

30
00:02:03,133 --> 00:02:04,933
No need to apologize.

31
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,233
What she said is true.

32
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,200
What my fashion critics said

33
00:02:10,267 --> 00:02:12,867
is that Aurelia is better
than me.

34
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:14,433
I'm a one-hit-wonder.

35
00:02:14,533 --> 00:02:15,100
I'm a nobody.

36
00:02:16,567 --> 00:02:19,867
- Love...
- Yeah, it's true.

37
00:02:19,933 --> 00:02:20,833
I know that.

38
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:24,400
I know that I also
don't deserve that.

39
00:02:24,467 --> 00:02:26,100
But you know...

40
00:02:26,167 --> 00:02:27,800
I don't know.

41
00:02:27,867 --> 00:02:29,800
With what your daughter said,
I'm just really trying

42
00:02:29,867 --> 00:02:32,800
to find my place with my career,

43
00:02:32,867 --> 00:02:33,667
with your family.

44
00:02:35,033 --> 00:02:38,567
Well at the end of the day,
what's important is you love me

45
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:39,767
and I love you, right?

46
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:45,233
Yes, but when we settle down
what will the people say?

47
00:02:45,300 --> 00:02:45,867
What do you mean?

48
00:02:47,733 --> 00:02:50,100
We both know
that I'm an underachiever.

49
00:02:50,167 --> 00:02:50,467
I'm...

50
00:02:52,233 --> 00:02:54,100
I'm a nobody and...

51
00:02:54,167 --> 00:02:56,533
I'm grateful for everything
that you've done for me

52
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:59,833
but everyone knows that I just
cling to your success

53
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:00,300
and I'm...

54
00:03:02,033 --> 00:03:05,333
I'm trying my best
to revitalize Celestial

55
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:11,233
but I'm just so uninspired
and so discouraged.

56
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,500
Love, we know
that when you create,

57
00:03:15,533 --> 00:03:17,967
you truly fulfill your purpose
in life.

58
00:03:19,333 --> 00:03:22,500
To spark your creativity
why don't you take a break?

59
00:03:23,900 --> 00:03:25,000
Maybe you want to travel

60
00:03:25,067 --> 00:03:26,700
to the fashion capital
of the world?

61
00:03:28,133 --> 00:03:28,333
What?

62
00:03:29,767 --> 00:03:31,700
We can fly to any destination

63
00:03:31,767 --> 00:03:35,500
where you can immerse yourself
in global fashion trends.

64
00:03:35,567 --> 00:03:38,133
You can bring along your staff
with you.

65
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:39,067
I will come with you.

66
00:03:42,300 --> 00:03:43,900
Are you serious?

67
00:03:43,967 --> 00:03:44,900
How about your work?

68
00:03:45,967 --> 00:03:46,933
I can manage.

69
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,367
Love, you matter to me

70
00:03:49,433 --> 00:03:52,133
and I will always find the time
to be with you.

71
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:56,333
So, are you going to accept
my offer?

72
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,300
Of course.

73
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,267
You made me so happy.

74
00:04:08,700 --> 00:04:11,233
I only want to make you
as happy as you made me.

75
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:47,900
So, when are you planning
to propose to Celeste?

76
00:04:50,367 --> 00:04:53,700
Soon. But at this point in time,

77
00:04:53,767 --> 00:04:55,533
I think it's more important
for me

78
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:58,033
to support her in her dreams.

79
00:04:58,100 --> 00:05:00,567
That's so magnanimous of you,
Tonito.

80
00:05:00,667 --> 00:05:03,867
The thing is, Celeste
might grow impatient.

81
00:05:03,933 --> 00:05:04,367
I'm telling you.

82
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:06,333
That won't happen.

83
00:05:07,567 --> 00:05:09,933
I know that Celeste
won't give up on our love.

84
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,667
She will not leave me.

85
00:05:11,733 --> 00:05:15,433
Unlike Aurelia
who easily gave up the marriage

86
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,433
for her ambition.

87
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:20,100
Well, to be fair with her,

88
00:05:20,167 --> 00:05:22,567
it was a mutual decision
on our part to end the marriage.

89
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,267
It just didn't work out.

90
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:28,733
We, your cousins,
admire you Tonito

91
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:30,567
with how good you handle things.

92
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:33,533
I can't imagine
how you even managed

93
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,467
to be friends with your ex-wife.

94
00:05:35,567 --> 00:05:39,133
It's better if we are friends
for Tiffany's sake.

95
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:41,467
But that would only bring
further complications

96
00:05:41,533 --> 00:05:43,000
in your relationship
with Celeste.

97
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:45,467
- Don't you think?
- Celeste and I are secured

98
00:05:45,533 --> 00:05:47,100
with our love for each other.

99
00:05:47,167 --> 00:05:49,067
For now, yes.

100
00:05:50,167 --> 00:05:52,767
But we both know that it will
never be easy for Celeste

101
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:54,567
to blend in with the family.

102
00:05:54,633 --> 00:05:58,233
So if I were you, don't delay
your proposal further.

103
00:05:59,633 --> 00:06:00,667
Seal the deal.

104
00:06:20,667 --> 00:06:20,933
Love?

105
00:06:24,033 --> 00:06:25,333
I'm just a bit nervous.

106
00:06:26,633 --> 00:06:27,300
Don't worry, Love.

107
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:29,300
I got you.

108
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:12,833
Let's all send
our birthday wishes

109
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:17,967
to the force behind our family's
fast-rising conglomerate.

110
00:07:18,067 --> 00:07:22,867
Our beloved Chairwoman and CEO,
Madam Vivian Tiongson-Wenceslao.

111
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,767
Good evening everyone

112
00:07:42,833 --> 00:07:45,667
and thank you so much
for coming to my party.

113
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:48,900
Let us enjoy the rest
of the night.

114
00:07:58,667 --> 00:08:00,100
Happy birthday, Vivian.

115
00:08:01,167 --> 00:08:04,433
I wish you a lifetime of health,
joy, and happiness.

116
00:08:05,433 --> 00:08:08,500
Happy birthday, Auntie Vivian.

117
00:08:12,967 --> 00:08:15,267
I thought that your mother
is here with you.

118
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:16,167
Where is she?

119
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:18,500
She's in the powder room.

120
00:08:18,567 --> 00:08:19,600
I'll just call her.

121
00:08:19,667 --> 00:08:22,200
No, stay here, Tiffany.

122
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:25,500
Tonito, you should call her.

123
00:08:25,567 --> 00:08:27,433
Sure. I'll be right back.

124
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:34,000
Happy Birthday, Vivian.

125
00:08:35,767 --> 00:08:36,867
Do not speak Chinese

126
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:39,933
if you don't know
how to pronounce it correctly.

127
00:08:41,433 --> 00:08:42,100
I'm sorry.

128
00:08:44,233 --> 00:08:46,000
How do you like my gown,
Celeste?

129
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:48,333
It's...

130
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,867
You look lovely, it's beautiful.

131
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:51,467
It's a classic.

132
00:08:53,233 --> 00:08:54,900
I thought so.

133
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,900
Aurelia was the one
who designed my gown.

134
00:08:57,967 --> 00:09:03,000
She makes most of my outfits
because she's simply the best.

135
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:14,800
They say as the crab walks,

136
00:09:16,367 --> 00:09:18,400
so walk his children.

137
00:09:18,467 --> 00:09:21,200
I've met you several times
before, Celeste.

138
00:09:21,267 --> 00:09:24,167
But I don't know you very well.

139
00:09:24,233 --> 00:09:25,833
Where is your family?

140
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:28,033
Do you live with them?

141
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:31,167
No, Ma'am. I don't live
with my family.

142
00:09:31,233 --> 00:09:32,500
Why are you not with them?

143
00:09:34,167 --> 00:09:37,233
Well, because my mother
passed when I was young.

144
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:37,800
No wonder.

145
00:09:38,867 --> 00:09:42,933
A daughter without a mother
is a broken woman.

146
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:46,733
I could smell from a mile away

147
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:49,633
that you're hiding something,
Celeste.

148
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:51,667
Tell me, what is your secret?

149
00:10:02,767 --> 00:10:04,200
I don't have any secrets
to hide.

150
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:08,033
Liar.

151
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:12,133
The heart of a woman
is an ocean full of secrets.

152
00:10:13,967 --> 00:10:16,433
You should separate from Tonito,
Celeste.

153
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:19,400
Because even with your
absolute very best,

154
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:24,067
you will still never be good
enough for my brother.

155
00:10:39,533 --> 00:10:41,033
Oh, there you are.

156
00:10:41,100 --> 00:10:42,967
- Oh, hi.
- Vivian has been looking

157
00:10:43,033 --> 00:10:45,700
- for you.
- Oh, no.

158
00:10:45,767 --> 00:10:48,367
it's embarrassing to face her.

159
00:10:48,433 --> 00:10:50,233
I've had too much wine.

160
00:10:51,533 --> 00:10:53,133
Am I blushing?

161
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,867
You look good.

162
00:10:54,933 --> 00:10:56,800
Good, not great?

163
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,467
Very well, you look great.

164
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:09,933
Aurelia, you're making me feel
uncomfortable.

165
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:13,300
Oh, I'm sorry.

166
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:18,200
Do you think I'm flirting
with you, Tonito?

167
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:20,967
I'm not, okay.

168
00:11:21,033 --> 00:11:21,667
Excuse me.

169
00:11:24,367 --> 00:11:25,567
No offense meant.

170
00:11:25,633 --> 00:11:28,233
We're friends but we need
to set healthy boundaries.

171
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:31,333
Yes, of course.

172
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,233
Hey, we're at a party.

173
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:35,200
You're not in a board room,
okay?

174
00:11:35,267 --> 00:11:36,367
Come on, let's go.

175
00:11:36,433 --> 00:11:39,233
Maybe your girlfriend
is looking for you.

176
00:11:39,300 --> 00:11:39,767
After you.

177
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:47,333
Stop crying.

178
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,667
This is not a funeral.

179
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:51,433
It's embarrassing.

180
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:56,833
Come here, Celeste.

181
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:57,533
Listen to me.

182
00:11:58,667 --> 00:12:03,333
My brother and Aurelia may have
mutually agreed to part ways.

183
00:12:03,400 --> 00:12:06,333
But for as long as I live,
I won't stop

184
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:09,067
until their family will get back
together again.

185
00:12:09,133 --> 00:12:10,733
You don't belong here, Celeste.

186
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:13,267
Do you understand?

187
00:12:24,667 --> 00:12:26,033
- How's everything?
- It's fine.

188
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:30,633
Tonito, Aurelia, Tiffany,

189
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:32,500
let's have a family picture
together.

190
00:12:33,733 --> 00:12:35,367
And...

191
00:12:35,433 --> 00:12:36,133
Winston.

192
00:12:42,667 --> 00:12:43,933
- Come on, Love.
- Go ahead.

193
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,367
Join us in the picture.

194
00:12:45,433 --> 00:12:46,867
Go ahead. You first.

195
00:12:46,933 --> 00:12:48,467
You're part of the family now.
Come on.

196
00:12:49,733 --> 00:12:51,600
Tonito, what's taking you
so long?

197
00:12:51,667 --> 00:12:53,500
- Go ahead. I'll join later.
- Are you sure you're okay?

198
00:12:53,567 --> 00:12:54,467
Yeah.

199
00:14:07,433 --> 00:14:08,633
Love, wait.

200
00:14:12,867 --> 00:14:13,900
I know you won't tell me

201
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:15,667
but you can't deny it.

202
00:14:16,767 --> 00:14:18,000
What did Vivian tell you?

203
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:20,433
I just want to go home.

204
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:20,700
No.

205
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:24,400
We will not go home
until Vivian and everyone else

206
00:14:24,467 --> 00:14:25,367
hears my piece.

207
00:14:26,933 --> 00:14:29,200
Love, trust me on this one.

208
00:15:25,233 --> 00:15:26,333
Your attention, please everyone.

209
00:15:28,267 --> 00:15:29,333
I'd like to propose a toast.

210
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:33,233
To the most amazing woman
that I know of,

211
00:15:34,867 --> 00:15:35,400
my sister.

212
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:40,533
Cheers!

213
00:15:42,133 --> 00:15:43,567
Cheers!

214
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:55,467
Vivian, I would like to thank
you for taking care of me

215
00:15:55,533 --> 00:15:58,000
since daddy and mommy died.

216
00:15:59,233 --> 00:16:03,867
You sacrificed a lot for me
and our family business.

217
00:16:03,933 --> 00:16:06,233
As well as having your own
family.

218
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,900
Men can build empires
and monuments

219
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,767
but these will all crumble
in time

220
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:16,033
but your legacy will endure
forever.

221
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:21,000
Vivian, we had lots
of differences

222
00:16:22,067 --> 00:16:25,000
but the love you taught me
will never die.

223
00:16:26,767 --> 00:16:29,200
Your love for me is your legacy.

224
00:16:29,267 --> 00:16:35,067
And that love is the reason
why I love now.

225
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:44,733
Celeste,

226
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:48,533
once in a lifetime,

227
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:50,267
right in the middle
of an ordinary life,

228
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:53,200
love gives you a fairy tale.

229
00:16:55,933 --> 00:16:59,500
Love, you have been my princess
for five long years.

230
00:17:00,633 --> 00:17:02,767
And I think, it's now time
to make you my queen.

231
00:17:09,467 --> 00:17:09,833
Celeste,

232
00:17:12,133 --> 00:17:13,867
will you be
my happily ever after?

233
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,400
Will you marry me?

234
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:42,333
Of course.

235
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:44,533
Yes.

236
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,667
Tiff...

237
00:18:42,733 --> 00:18:43,100
Tiff...

238
00:18:44,067 --> 00:18:45,367
Tiff, can you please wait.

239
00:18:46,867 --> 00:18:47,933
Tiff.

240
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:48,600
Tiffany!

241
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,400
Don't leave.

242
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,833
Your Auntie Vivian
will look for you, okay?

243
00:18:57,867 --> 00:19:02,167
Mom, do you really expect me
to go back to the party?

244
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:03,733
After what dad did?

245
00:19:05,100 --> 00:19:06,267
Don't you feel insulted?

246
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:11,333
Tiff, I have no right
to feel that way.

247
00:19:12,367 --> 00:19:14,367
Your dad and I
are already annulled.

248
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:17,733
Mom, don't you love him anymore?

249
00:19:22,933 --> 00:19:24,433
You still love him, don't you?

250
00:19:25,733 --> 00:19:27,100
Mom, you still love my dad.

251
00:19:32,100 --> 00:19:33,833
Tiff, I...

252
00:19:36,433 --> 00:19:37,667
I refuse to answer that.

253
00:19:42,133 --> 00:19:44,433
I don't want to give you
false hope

254
00:19:44,500 --> 00:19:48,433
that your dad and I
will get back together, okay?

255
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:49,900
You will just hurt more.

256
00:19:49,967 --> 00:19:53,000
The more I will get hurt
if you will not do anything

257
00:19:53,067 --> 00:19:54,433
for you and Dad
to get back together.

258
00:20:31,867 --> 00:20:35,467
Celeste, maybe that flawless
diamond ring

259
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:36,733
will melt with you
staring at it.

260
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:40,400
Dear, I am just amazed.

261
00:20:40,467 --> 00:20:44,367
It's so surreal
that I'm engaged to Tonito.

262
00:20:44,433 --> 00:20:45,367
Can you imagine?

263
00:20:47,300 --> 00:20:49,833
By the way,
where's the itinerary?

264
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:53,100
Well yeah, I'm actually fixing
our travel bookings.

265
00:20:53,167 --> 00:20:55,867
And we'll fly to Paris
first week of next month.

266
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:57,800
Wait.

267
00:20:57,867 --> 00:20:58,933
No, we cannot.

268
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,600
You have to cancel that
or you know what,

269
00:21:00,667 --> 00:21:03,300
move it this month because
I have to focus on the wedding,

270
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:04,567
all the planning.

271
00:21:04,633 --> 00:21:06,900
I have to get married to Tonito
within the year.

272
00:21:06,967 --> 00:21:09,967
Celeste,
you're not that excited.

273
00:21:10,067 --> 00:21:11,100
Of course, I'm excited.

274
00:21:11,167 --> 00:21:18,733
I cannot wait to just
get married and wake up

275
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:21,733
and see the man of my dreams
every day.

276
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,500
Oh, so sweet.

277
00:21:25,967 --> 00:21:28,400
But, Dear, the question is...

278
00:21:29,633 --> 00:21:31,533
are you ready for the war
you are about to get into?

279
00:21:42,433 --> 00:21:44,100
Flowers for you.

280
00:21:44,167 --> 00:21:45,600
That's so nice.

281
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:52,033
Thank you so much.

282
00:21:52,100 --> 00:21:55,467
Love, what do you think
I should do

283
00:21:56,667 --> 00:22:01,667
for your sister, Vivian,
and Tiffany to accept me?

284
00:22:03,433 --> 00:22:07,000
Love, you don't have to prove
anything to my sister,

285
00:22:07,067 --> 00:22:09,067
my daughter, or anybody else.

286
00:22:09,133 --> 00:22:12,233
If my family doesn't treat you
right, worse comes to worst,

287
00:22:12,300 --> 00:22:15,600
I'll give up my position,
my inheritance, the perks.

288
00:22:16,833 --> 00:22:20,700
I'm willing to give up
everything to prove to you

289
00:22:20,767 --> 00:22:21,800
how much I love you.

290
00:22:23,733 --> 00:22:26,333
I appreciate all of that
and all the support.

291
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:29,933
It's just that I don't want you
to give up

292
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,967
or sacrifice your relationship
with your family because of me.

293
00:22:34,167 --> 00:22:40,067
Let's just pray
that everything will be fine.

294
00:22:40,133 --> 00:22:45,400
Well, if my family can't accept
you as my future wife,

295
00:22:45,467 --> 00:22:46,800
life will still go on for us.

296
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:49,633
Come hell or high water

297
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,600
our wedding will push through.

298
00:23:09,567 --> 00:23:10,067
Yes.

299
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:14,767
Oh my God, Jamaica.
This is so good.

300
00:23:14,833 --> 00:23:19,000
This is such a good fashion
campaign.

301
00:23:19,067 --> 00:23:22,433
This is perfect. So, while we're
immersing ourselves abroad

302
00:23:22,533 --> 00:23:24,867
with all of the new fashion
trends.

303
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,733
When the clients see this,
they won't feel

304
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:29,400
that we've been gone for two
months.

305
00:23:29,467 --> 00:23:31,733
Yes, and I think
this is a good counteraction

306
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:34,667
against bad fashion reviews
that came out.

307
00:23:34,733 --> 00:23:35,733
Perfect.

308
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:37,400
Okay, so we're set.

309
00:23:37,467 --> 00:23:38,900
So our trip is set
for next week.

310
00:23:38,967 --> 00:23:40,233
Yes, of course.

311
00:23:42,433 --> 00:23:45,400
I think that's my phone.

312
00:23:46,167 --> 00:23:47,467
Sorry, it's there, sorry.

313
00:23:47,533 --> 00:23:48,433
Thank you, Jamaica.

314
00:23:53,167 --> 00:23:53,933
Thank you.

315
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:04,867
Hello, Sebastian?

316
00:24:04,933 --> 00:24:06,333
Hello, Celeste?

317
00:24:08,900 --> 00:24:10,300
Why did you call?

318
00:24:10,367 --> 00:24:10,767
Celeste,

319
00:24:12,767 --> 00:24:15,300
they are going to the provincial
hospital right now.

320
00:24:15,367 --> 00:24:18,600
- Father had a heart attack.
- Father...

321
00:24:19,633 --> 00:24:24,167
Celeste, mother and I don't know
what to do.

322
00:24:24,233 --> 00:24:25,533
We need your help.

323
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:30,967
Celeste, you need to come home
here in Sorsogon.

324
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,267
What?

325
00:24:33,333 --> 00:24:34,433
Sorsogon?

326
00:24:52,033 --> 00:24:53,700
Book me a flight to Manila now.

327
00:24:53,767 --> 00:24:56,100
I thought you're going to stay
in Sorsogon for two more days.

328
00:24:56,167 --> 00:24:57,633
I have no more business here.

329
00:24:57,700 --> 00:25:00,233
There's no reason for me to stay
for another day.

330
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:01,967
This isn't my home anymore.

331
00:25:02,067 --> 00:25:04,400
Cousin, come on.
Let's talk first.

332
00:25:04,467 --> 00:25:05,567
Hurry, come on.

333
00:25:05,633 --> 00:25:08,200
How does Mikoy look like now?

334
00:25:08,267 --> 00:25:12,167
Well, your ex
still looks handsome.

335
00:25:12,233 --> 00:25:13,167
He's yummy!

336
00:25:14,267 --> 00:25:16,567
I'm happy with what I'm doing
right now. How about you?

337
00:25:16,633 --> 00:25:19,700
Sorry, what? Are you asking me
if I'm happy?

338
00:25:19,767 --> 00:25:21,333
Yes, of course.

339
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:22,833
Super. I'm super happy.

340
00:25:22,900 --> 00:25:25,967
I mean, the best times
of my life.

341
00:25:26,033 --> 00:25:28,867
I've never been this happy ever
actually.

342
00:25:28,933 --> 00:25:31,433
There was no spark at all?

343
00:25:31,500 --> 00:25:34,233
- Nothing.
- There was no pinch?

344
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:36,100
You should admit the truth.

345
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:38,400
I said nothing. What's with you?
Celeste is getting married.

346
00:25:38,467 --> 00:25:40,933
Have you seen the tarp
in the newly built

347
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:43,333
Grand replica chapel
in Sitio Guibalot?

348
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:44,600
Not yet, Mayor.

349
00:25:44,667 --> 00:25:47,300
You should see that because
you look so handsome there.

350
00:25:47,367 --> 00:25:49,300
Really, are you stalking me?

351
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:52,800
Why are you looking at me
that way?

352
00:25:52,867 --> 00:25:55,000
Do you think you're handsome?

353
00:25:55,067 --> 00:25:56,833
You're not cute! Ugly!

354
00:25:56,900 --> 00:25:59,667
Your wife-to-be
is really very lucky, Mikoy.

355
00:25:59,733 --> 00:26:01,433
You are very hardworking.

356
00:26:01,500 --> 00:26:05,133
You are also handsome.
You never run out of talent.

357
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:06,800
Do you want us to be a couple?

358
00:26:06,867 --> 00:26:07,667
Seriously!

359
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:10,567
Celeste?

360
00:26:11,767 --> 00:26:12,600
Oh my God!
